const headHtml = "<title>Auction House Flipping Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026</title>\n    <meta name=\"description\" content=\"An expert based 2026 Auction House flipping guide for Hypixel SkyBlock covering manual search loops, post-tax pricing, item liquidity, BIN comparisons and the live tools that help you flip more confidently.\">\n    <link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/ah-flipping-guide-2026\">\n\n    <meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/ah-flipping-guide-2026\">\n    <meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\">\n    <meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Auction House Flipping Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026\">\n    <meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Learn the AH flipping workflow that still works in 2026: narrow filters, clear resale bands, tax awareness and live data for faster pricing decisions.\">\n    <meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/static/NEC.png\">\n    <script type=\"application/ld+json\">\n      {\n        \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\",\n        \"@type\": \"BlogPosting\",\n        \"headline\": \"Auction House Flipping Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026\",\n        \"description\": \"Expert based guide to manual AH flipping, price recognition and resale discipline in Hypixel SkyBlock.\",\n        \"datePublished\": \"2026-01-05\",\n        \"dateModified\": \"2026-04-18\",\n        \"author\": {\n          \"@type\": \"Organization\",\n          \"name\": \"NotEnoughCoins\"\n        },\n        \"publisher\": {\n          \"@type\": \"Organization\",\n          \"name\": \"Coflnet GmbH\"\n        },\n        \"url\": \"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/ah-flipping-guide-2026\"\n      }\n    </script>";
const bodyHtml = "<main>\n      <div class=\"site-shell article-layout\">\n        <article class=\"article\">\n          <a class=\"article-meta\" href=\"/guides#months-list\">2026-01-05 • AH Flipping</a>\n          <h1>Auction House Flipping Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026</h1>\n          <p class=\"lede\">Auction House flipping is still one of the best active money methods in Hypixel SkyBlock, but the reliable profit is not hiding inside a static item list. It comes from narrowing the market to items you understand, checking whether the resale band is real, and pricing with taxes and sell speed in mind. The players who win consistently do not buy whatever looks green on a screenshot. They price faster, pass more often, and only buy when the whole trade makes sense.</p>\n\n          <div class=\"note\">\n            <strong>Primary source base:</strong> FarmerWarden's broad flipping guide, fightBck's auction walkthrough and kiutn's breakdown of normal flips, BIN sniping and lowball-assisted discovery.\n          </div>\n\n          <h2>What strong AH flipping actually looks like</h2>\n          <p>The heart of Auction House flipping is not memorizing a single profitable item. It is learning how a small group of items behaves: how often they sell, which modifiers matter, what buyers will actually pay for recombs or stars, and where the next believable resale level begins. Once you understand a narrow market segment, the browser becomes easier to read and bad listings stop looking tempting.</p>\n          <p>This is why good creator guides keep returning to the same principle. A true flip is not just an item listed below the first visible price. It is an item listed below a believable resale band that still leaves room after tax, undercutting and relist friction. If that band is weak, your profit is only a screenshot.</p>\n\n          <h2>Build a repeatable search loop</h2>\n          <p>The safest routine is simple. Filter into a category you understand, compare the cheapest active listings against recent market context, decide your post-tax target before you buy, then only enter if you can resell aggressively without killing the margin. That sounds obvious, but it removes most of the emotional mistakes that drain coins from newer flippers.</p>\n          <p>A repeatable loop also makes AH flipping less stressful. Instead of refreshing everything and hoping for a miracle, you rotate through controlled searches: specific accessories, utility weapons, dungeon pieces, skins or low-supply items with clear buyer pools. The result is slower than pure gambling, but far more stable over a full week of sessions.</p>\n\n          <h2>Know when to pass on a listing</h2>\n          <p>Most profitable AH sessions are built as much on skipped buys as on successful flips. If the next cheapest listing is too close, if the item is too niche, if the resale relies on perfect timing, or if taxes erase most of the spread, passing is the correct move. That discipline is what separates controlled flipping from accidental warehousing.</p>\n          <p>It is also why AH flipping pairs so well with bazaar and craft knowledge. Once you understand spread depth, buyer urgency and capital rotation from other methods, you stop chasing every cheap listing and start asking better questions about exit quality. That shift alone is worth millions over time.</p>\n\n          <h2>Use live tools to compress the pricing work</h2>\n          <p>Live tools do not replace judgment, but they make judgment faster. <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/flipper\">SkyCofl AH flipper</a> is excellent for modifier-aware price context, <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/lowSupply\">low supply</a> surfaces thin markets where pricing power matters, <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/recentFlips\">recent flips</a> helps validate whether the live feed is active, and <a href=\"https://pro.skyblock.bz/features/auction-flips\">BazaarPro auction flips</a> wraps the same workflow inside a rules-driven dashboard. Use them to shorten the reference check, not to outsource the decision.</p>\n\n          <h2>Read next</h2>\n          <ul class=\"related-list\">\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/bazaar-flipping-guide-2026\">Bazaar Flipping Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026</a></li>\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/bin-sniping-guide-2026\">BIN Sniping Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026</a></li>\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/lowballing-and-flip-discovery\">Lowballing and Flip Discovery in Hypixel SkyBlock</a></li>\n          </ul>\n        </article>\n\n        <aside class=\"article-aside\">\n          <div>\n            <h3>Best paired tools</h3>\n            <ul class=\"tool-list\">\n              <li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/flipper\">SkyCofl AH flipper</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/flips\">SkyCofl flips hub</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/lowSupply\">SkyCofl low supply</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/recentFlips\">SkyCofl recent flips</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/subscriptions\">SkyCofl notifiers</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://pro.skyblock.bz/features/auction-flips\">BazaarPro auction flips</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/auctions\">BazaarTracker auctions</a></li>\n            </ul>\n          </div>\n          <div>\n            <h3>Best for</h3>\n            <p>Players who want an active money method with flexible capital requirements and enough market control to improve through repetition.</p>\n          </div>\n          <div>\n            <h3>Source videos</h3>\n            <p>FarmerWarden, fightBck and kiutn form the backbone here because they explain the pricing process, not just item names.</p>\n          </div>\n        </aside>\n      </div>\n    </main>";
